                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 3: The Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority (PFRDA) will come out with investment guidelines for its mega pension plan by the middle of this month. Investment guidelines will be finalised by the middle of this month. The scheme will be launched on May 1, PFRDA chairman D. Swarup said.                             
	 New Delhi, April 3: Sun Pharmaceutical has extended the open offer for acquiring shares of Taro Pharmaceutical, which was scheduled to expire today, to April 17. Alkalolda Chemical Company Exclusive Group, a subsidiary firm of Sun Pharma, has extended the expiry date of the tender offer.                            
	 New Delhi, April 3: Corporate India raised $17.58 billion from abroad in 2008-09, almost half of what was raised in 2007-08. The funds raised through various securities have fallen 47.66 per cent to $17.58 billion from $33.59 billion a year ago.                            
	 New Delhi, April 3: The ICAI has clarified that the exemption from AS11 is only for corporates and not for non- corporate bodies such as partnership firms. They (non-corporate assessees) will continue showing losses (or gains as may the case) according to Accounting Standard 11, ICAI president Uttam Prakash Agarwal said.                            
